
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `debcommit` baraye sakhtan (`create`) commit message-haye standard baraye taghirat dar package-haye Debian estefade mishavad. Yani komak mikonad ta commit message-haye shoma moratab va ba format-e moshakhas bashad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `debcommit`  --> 📝 Commit message-e sade misazad (agar message ra vared nakonid, az shoma soal mikonad).
    🔹 `debcommit -a` --> ➕ Hameye taghirat-e stag shode ra ezafe mikonad va commit mikonad.
    🔹 `debcommit -e` --> ✏️ Commit message-e ghablee ra edit mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ debcommit

    🔹 Commit message-e jadid misazad. Shoma bayad message ra vared konid.

    $ debcommit -a -m "Fix: address security vulnerability"

    🔹 Hameye taghirat-e stage shode ra commit mikonad ba commit message "Fix: address security vulnerability".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ debcommit -a -m "feat: Add support for Persian language"

    🔹 In dastoor hameye taghirat-e stage shode ra commit mikonad va yek commit message ba format-e munasib misazad ("feat: Add support for Persian language").

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debcommit` command is used to create standardized commit messages for changes in Debian packages. It helps ensure that your commit messages are consistent and follow a specific format.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `debcommit`  --> 📝 Creates a simple commit message (if no message is provided, it will prompt you).
    🔹 `debcommit -a` --> ➕ Adds all staged changes and commits them.
    🔹 `debcommit -e` --> ✏️ Edits the previous commit message.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debcommit

    🔹 Creates a new commit message. You will be prompted to enter the message.

    $ debcommit -a -m "Fix: address security vulnerability"

    🔹 Commits all staged changes with the commit message "Fix: address security vulnerability".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ debcommit -a -m "feat: Add support for Persian language"

    🔹 This command commits all staged changes and creates a commit message in a suitable format ("feat: Add support for Persian language").

